"(1) The night draped itself in a gauzy, electric hush, the open sky reflected in the shimmering river of city lights far below. Along the elevated promenade, steel and glass rose into the cool air like a skyline reborn—this was the High Line, transformed tonight into a maze of polished tables and the murmur of ambition. Logan paused at the threshold, his breath visible in the faint chill, catching the scent of jasmine from a flickering centerpiece as he adjusted the cuff of his dark jacket. He had worn it with a sense of occasion he hadn’t known he possessed, the fabric soft against his skin as it caught the occasional glint of light from above.\n\n(2) Beneath the arches of the High Line’s concrete overhangs, chandeliers cast a honeyed glow over the sea of tailored suits and sleek power-dresses. Laughter and low conversation tumbled across tables draped in white linen, the air thick with the anticipation of deals and the subtle thrill of new acquaintances. A band’s opening notes floated upward from a secluded lounge, mingling with the bracing cold and the clink of crystal. Logan moved through it like a ghost, noting the way the city’s heartbeat seemed amplified here—each step echoing not only on the polished floors, but in the steady rhythm of possibility.\n\n(3) He took his seat at a round table ringed by sleek laptops and coffee cups, the hostess’s smile guiding him to a place among rising entrepreneurs and seasoned moguls. As he glanced at the unfamiliar faces, Logan felt a flutter in his chest—a nervous electricity that had nothing to do with the city’s pulse but everything to do with the unknown. A woman nearby adjusted her pearl earring, catching his eye with a knowing tilt of her head. He offered a small nod and kept his hands steady, refusing the urge to reach for his phone or introduce himself.\n\n(4) The evening unfolded with a ballet of business ritual: presentations flickered on a screen, projections mapping out future trends in fintech and sustainable packaging. Logan listened, mind half-distracted by the scent of fresh coffee mingling with the metallic tang of ambition. The lights here felt softer, almost intimate, as if the High Line was its own world—one that held secrets in its shadowed corners, whispers carried on the breeze. Every exchange was calculated, every smile a mask of intent.\n\n(5) Between structured talks, he drifted toward an open area where drinks shimmered in crystal glasses,"